Title: Necessity is the Mother of Invention Ep.3
SubTitle: No Translation

Text:
Three days have passed since Eta shut herself in
her laboratory.

This isn't at all unusualâ€”she's always been the type
to hole herself up in her room whenever she isn't
out on some kind of mission.

This is why the lab doubles as her private bedroom,
a single room just for her.
To make the power...micro-sized...

But whenever Eta is buried in research, the room
becomes nothing but a laboratory.
She simply does not move away from her desk.
Eta, I've brought you some food.

Epsilon enters the room without so much as knockingâ€”
she knows that there would be no point.

The tray in her hand holds sandwiches and a glass
of milk.
Oh? I can see the floor today.

What happened to all the papers lying about? Did you
tidy them up?
...Gamma...
Gamma? Ah, now that you mention it...

Since I wasn't able to come yesterday, it was Gamma
who brought you your food.
And so she cleaned for you as well.
...She fell...and spilt everything...
...The food, you mean?
Yeah.
Oh I see. Sounds like Gamma alright.
And so she tidied up a little as well.
Everything's...in a strange...place.

Shush, you. She tidied up for you, so look at it as
a positive.
Hmmm...

As usual, Eta carries out her part of the conversation
without even raising her head. She stares at her desk,
eyes on the research project that is reaching its climax.
Epsilon brings the food closer.

It's sandwiches, so you can eat them with one hand.
Come on, hold out your handâ€”
...Yikes!
Catching sight of Eta's face, Epsilon's eyes widen.
Those bags under your eyes!
...Sandwich...

Yelping in shock, Epsilon comes closer. Eta glances
at her and reaches out for a sandwich.
More importantly! Your eyes! They're crazy black!
Hm?
Did you pull an all-nighter last night?!
Hm?

And the night before?! The day I warmed up the bread
for you!

While you were eating, you told me that you'd take a
nap once your research got to a good stopping point!
Well...that's what I thought...

But I was...making great progress...after eating that
bread...
So you stayed up all night?

Last night...two nights ago...that's three nights in
a row?!
...I've lost track...of time...but I guess so.
Goodness... I'm astounded to say the least.
Come on... Sandwich...
...All right. Here you go.

Letting out a sigh of exasperation, Epsilon places
the tray of sandwiches and milk on the desk.

Taking a sandwich in one hand, Eta absently takes
a bite. All the while, her other hand is like a storm,
scribbling complex formulas down on the paper
before her.
*munch, munch*
How's the taste?
...Normal.

Just say it's delicious, will you. I mean, I brought
it all the way here for you.
...Right. ...*munch*

Glancing at the profile of her colleague, cheeks
stuffed full of sandwich, Epsilon sighs again.

A lack of sleep is the enemy of beauty. I can't
believe you've given yourself such heavy bags...
Why do you bury yourself in research like this?

To the point where you lose all sense of time, eating
away at your private life and the time you should be
taking to look after yourself...

There are...lots of things in this world...that
I don't know.
And I want to know...everything.
Everything?
Yeah... Everything.

If I succeed...in my research...then there will be...
one less unknown.

You know...that's something pretty outrageous
you're saying there.
Okay.
Eta nods firmlyâ€”at least, that's how Epsilon sees it.

(Well, this sheer sincerity of hers grabs my heart so
much that I'd do everything I can to help take care
of the rest.)
...Hmm...? What...is it?
Oh... Nothing.
...That so?

Embarrassed at the thought that Eta might guess
what she was thinking, Epsilon shakes her head.

But Eta simply digs into her second sandwich, as if
she hasn't noticed anything amiss.
Ack, you've got sauce on your cheek.
...Okay. I'll...wipe it off...later.

Best wipe it off now. Come on, turn your head
this way.
...I can do it...myself.
Wait! Not with your sleeve!

In the blink of an eye, Eta's arm is locked in place,
halfway to her cheek.

Taking out her handkerchief, Epsilon proceeds to
wipe Eta's cheek for her.
Mmph...mhm...
This handkerchief...smells nice...

It's something every lady should have. How about
you try carrying one yourself?
...In my pocket?

Heh... If you did that, I'm sure it'd be all crumpled
up in no time.

Epsilon laughs, her shoulders heaving slightly, as the
image easily comes to her mind.
...Sure... *munch, munch*

Bemused at her reaction, Eta continues to eat in
silence.

When they are all gone, she licks her fingers and
downs the milk.
...Right. Nutrient intake...complete.
Come on now, call it a meal.
...Either works. Now...back to work.
You're not planning to get any sleep at all, are you?
Yeah.
Eta nods, in spite of the massive bags under her eyes.

...Just a bit...more. Right now...is the most
exciting...part.
Then there's no point trying to stop you.

So make sure you report to everyone when you're
done. We need to let everyone know just how hard
you've worked!
...Doesn't matter. I'm not...doing this...for praise.

But...if I show them...what I've done...I'll get more
funding.
And for that, you've got to stay on your feet.

So I'll keep an eye on you. I'm in between missions
after all, and have nothing else planned.
You won't...tidy up...without my permission?
Nope.
Alright... Then you...can stay.

Muttering her acquiescence, Eta wipes her slightly
damp hands on her clothes and returns to her work.
Goodness. What do you think handkerchiefs are for?

But Epsilon's voice no longer reaches the ears of the
scientist, whose focus is back on the research project
in front of her.
